  "narrative": {
    "intro": "Federal contract obligations in Idaho for FY2026 to date total $3B. Obligations are down 23.5% year over year, with 7,818 awards and an average award size of $381K. The Department of Energy accounts for the largest share of buying activity at $2.3B, while the Department of Agriculture follows at $363M and the Department of Defense at $115M. BATTELLE ENERGY ALLIANCE, LLC is the largest contractor with $1.8B in obligations, and IDAHO ENVIRONMENTAL COALITION LLC is the second-largest with $526M. Professional, scientific, and technical services lead industry spending at $1.8B, and Remediation Services total $532M. Historical fiscal-year obligations show variation: FY21 was $2.8B, FY22 was $2.5B, FY23 was $3.2B, FY24 was $3.8B, FY25 was $3.9B, and FY26 to date is $3B. Several aviation and remediation firms appear among the top vendors and industries, reflecting concentrated program-level work. All figures are contract obligations; current-year totals are partial (fiscal year to date).",
    "sections": [
      {
        "heading": "What explains the FY2026 obligations profile in Idaho?",
        "body": "The Department of Energy drives the FY2026 obligations profile with $2.3B in buying activity. Overall obligations total $3B and are down 23.5% year over year, with 7,818 awards and an average award size of $381K. Historical fiscal-year totals show FY25 at $3.9B and FY24 at $3.8B, indicating the current year is lower than the two prior full fiscal years. The concentration of spending in a few buyers and vendors produces large single-vendor and single-agency shares of statewide obligations."
      },
      {
        "heading": "Which vendors and industries dominate federal spending in Idaho?",
        "body": "BATTELLE ENERGY ALLIANCE, LLC leads vendors with $1.8B in obligations, and IDAHO ENVIRONMENTAL COALITION LLC follows with $526M. The top industry is All Other Professional, Scientific, and Technical Services at $1.8B, with Remediation Services at $532M and Nonscheduled Chartered Freight Air Transportation at $223M. Several aviation services and construction-related NAICS appear in the top 10, reflecting program-focused procurement."
      }
